{
  "texts": [
    "stLearn [28], SpaGCN [29], DeepST [30], and STAGATE [31] adopt deep learning approaches to identify spatial domains.",
    "The latter three are based on graph neural networks, and they construct neighborhood graphs of cells or spots based on their spatial adjacency.",
    "This process can be time-consuming for datasets with large numbers of cells or spots.",
    "Some other methods combine gene expression and spatial information into a new feature matrix or latent representation that can be used for clustering and other follow-up analyses.",
    "For instance, UTAG [32] calculates an inner product between the spatial adjacency matrix and the expression matrix, returning a new matrix of spatially aggregated expression values."
  ]
}